{"uuid": "930c27f3-87fb-4202-8e48-00555928cd1e", "id": 9380, "date": "2019-04-28T05:00:00", "date_gmt": "2019-04-28T12:00:00", "guid": {"rendered": "http://estreetshuffle.com/?p=9380"}, "modified": "2019-04-28T17:00:29", "modified_gmt": "2019-04-29T00:00:29", "slug": "roll-of-the-dice-everybodys-looking-for-somebody", "status": "publish", "type": "post", "link": "https://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/2019/04/28/roll-of-the-dice-everybodys-looking-for-somebody/", "title": {"rendered": "Roll of the Dice: Everybody&#8217;s Looking for Somebody"}, "content": {"rendered": "<p>Actually, it&#8217;s not at all clear to me that&nbsp;<em>anybody&#8217;s&nbsp;</em>looking for somebody.</p>\n<p>This demo was recorded in Bruce&#8217;s home studio in Holmdel in late 1979. Fans have dubbed it &#8220;Everybody&#8217;s Looking for Somebody&#8221; (after what appears to be the refrain) or alternatively, &#8220;Blackwood&#8221; (after what appears to be a location mentioned in the song.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s the thing, though: I&#8217;ve listened to this thing waaaay more times than a 45-second, half-bluffed demo warrants, and I&#8217;m pretty darn sure Bruce is&nbsp;<em>not</em> saying &#8220;everybody&#8217;s looking for somebody.&#8221;</p>\n<p>Whatever everybody is looking for, it&#8217;s closer to &#8220;Blackwood&#8221; than &#8220;somebody,&#8221; but I don&#8217;t think it&#8217;s the name of a place, either.</p>\n<p>To me, the first syllable in whatever everybody&#8217;s looking for sounds like &#8220;night,&#8221; which would be in keeping with Bruce&#8217;s at-the-time fascination with things that happen after dark. But I can&#8217;t be sure, and I can&#8217;t for the life of me figure out the other syllable.</p>\n<p>So please give it a shot, and then you tell me. Take a listen below, and leave a comment if you think you know what Bruce is saying.</p>\n<div id=\"v-cFNkYdxa-1\" class=\"video-player\"><iframe title='VideoPress Video Player' aria-label='VideoPress Video Player' width='758' height='426' src='https://videopress.com/embed/cFNkYdxa?hd=1&amp;cover=1&amp;loop=0&amp;autoPlay=0&amp;permalink=1&amp;muted=0&amp;controls=1&amp;playsinline=0&amp;useAverageColor=0&amp;preloadContent=metadata' frameborder='0' allowfullscreen data-resize-to-parent=\"true\" allow='clipboard-write'></iframe><script data-jetpack-boost=\"ignore\" src='https://s0.wp.com/wp-content/plugins/video/assets/js/next/videopress-iframe.js'></script></div>\n<p><strong>Everybody&#8217;s Looking for ???<br />\nRecorded:</strong> September-December 1979<br />\n<strong>Never released</strong><br />\n<strong>Never performed</strong></p>\n<p>Looking for your favorite Bruce song? Check our&nbsp;<a href=\"http://estreetshuffle.com/index.php/roll-of-the-dice-album-by-album/\">full index</a>. New entries every week!</p>\n", "protected": false}, "excerpt": {"rendered": "<p>Everybody&#8217;s looking for *something*, but I&#8217;ll be darned if I can figure out what. Give this brief home demo a listen and see if you can figure out what Bruce is singing about.</p>\n", "protected": false}, "author": 1, "featured_media": 9613, "comment_status": "open", "ping_status": "open", "sticky": false, "template": "", "format": "standard", "meta": {"_monsterinsights_skip_tracking": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_active": false, "_monsterinsights_sitenote_note": "", "_monsterinsights_sitenote_category": 0, "jetpack_post_was_ever_published": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_access": "", "_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs": false, "_jetpack_newsletter_tier_id": 0, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paywalled_content": false, "_jetpack_memberships_contains_paid_content": false, "footnotes": "", "jetpack_publicize_message": "", "jetpack_publicize_feature_enabled": true, "jetpack_social_post_already_shared": true, "jetpack_social_options": {"image_generator_settings": {"template": "highway", "default_image_id": 0, "font": "", "enabled": false}, "version": 2}}, "categories": [3], "tags": [2318], "class_list":